<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="120" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="13.[136,1452,223,826]" box="[189,573,331,358]" pageId="13" pageNumber="120">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,381,331,358]" pageId="13" pageNumber="120">Common name:</emphasis>
—Sponge gourd.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[136,1452,223,826]" box="[189,1259,367,394]" pageId="13" pageNumber="120">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,291,367,393]" pageId="13" pageNumber="120">Habitat:</emphasis>
—Waste dump sites, uncompleted buildings, unpainted fences, roadsides, fallow bush.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[136,1452,223,826]" pageId="13" pageNumber="120">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,337,403,429]" pageId="13" pageNumber="120">Description:</emphasis>
—Herb, trailing and climbing; moenoecious. 
<emphasis box="[888,942,404,430]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="120">Stem</emphasis>
herbaceous, climbing, pubescent, angular, 
<quantity box="[136,264,439,466]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="13" pageNumber="120" unit="cm" value="0.44999999999999996" valueMax="0.6" valueMin="0.3">0.3–0.6 cm</quantity>
diam.; tendrils 3- to 4-fid, spirally coiled. 
<emphasis box="[762,840,440,465]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="120">Leaves</emphasis>
simple, alternately arranged, petiolate, hairy on both surfaces, palmately lobed with 5 joined lobes, green, apex acute, margin dentate, 8.2–17 × 
<quantity box="[1134,1233,476,502]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" metricValueMax="1.9" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="13" pageNumber="120" unit="cm" value="14.0" valueMax="19.0" valueMin="9.0">9–19 cm</quantity>
; petiole cylindrical, herbaceous, 
<quantity box="[278,363,512,538]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="13" pageNumber="120" unit="cm" value="6.0" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="4.0">4–8 cm</quantity>
long, hairy. 
<emphasis box="[509,659,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="120">Inflorescence</emphasis>
racemose for male flowers with about 5–20 flower buds, solitary for female flowers; pedunculate, peduncle 
<quantity box="[584,697,548,574]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.05" metricValueMax="3.1" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="13" pageNumber="120" unit="cm" value="20.5" valueMax="31.0" valueMin="10.0">10–31 cm</quantity>
long; 
<emphasis box="[773,854,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="120">pedicel</emphasis>
1.5–2.0 cm long; flowers 3 × 
<quantity box="[1207,1296,548,574]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="8.0" pageId="13" pageNumber="120" unit="cm" value="8.5" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="8.0">8–9 cm</quantity>
; calyx with 5 green, free sepals; corolla with 5 yellow, free imbricate petals, pubescent on both surfaces, 3–5 × 
<quantity box="[1223,1308,584,610]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="13" pageNumber="120" unit="cm" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2–4 cm</quantity>
, androecium parts 5. 
<emphasis box="[229,287,620,645]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="120">Fruit</emphasis>
pepos, cylindrical, green when fresh, brown and paper-like when dry, produces sponge bearing many seeds. 
<emphasis box="[211,264,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="120">Seed</emphasis>
flat, black.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[136,1452,223,826]" pageId="13" pageNumber="120">
