<collectingRegion box="[339,486,691,718]" country="Nigeria" name="Akwa Ibom" pageId="13" pageNumber="120">Akwa Ibom</collectingRegion>
:—
</emphasis>
Ini, Essien Udim, Oruk Anam, Obot Akara, Ikot Ekpene, Ibiono, Uyo, Ibesikpo Asutan, Nsit Atai, Nsit Ubium, Mkpat Enin, Ikot Abasi, Oron, Mbo, and 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:0167F2535733FFD2FF2EFF08FE53FC9D:8C11159E5733FFD2FC1EFD4EFBC9FD56" box="[952,1117,727,754]" name="Eastern Obolo" pageId="13" pageNumber="120" stateProvince="Akwa Ibom">Eastern Obolo</location>
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[136,1452,223,826]" pageId="13" pageNumber="120">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,364,763,789]" pageId="13" pageNumber="120">Abundance:—</emphasis>
It existed in 100% of the sampling areas, where it was abundant in 73%, frequent in 21%, and rare in 6% of the sampling areas.
</paragraph>
